  "chunk_index": 35,
  "summary": "Following a tense exchange with Yuzu regarding their relationship, Hagoromo agrees to meet her on the other side of the lake after sunset. While returning to his room, Hagoromo encounters MacArthur, who provocatively claims to be the best detective in Japan, surpassing Wakimura. MacArthur mentions he has spoken to Kanou regarding a client's disappearance, though Hagoromo suspects Muto has simply abandoned the client to hide in the mountains. Before retreating, MacArthur issues a cryptic warning to Hagoromo to pay attention to \"the twins.\"\n\nAt approximately 4 pm, Jia arrives in a panic to report that Kaina and Wanli are missing. The household falls into chaos; Kaname attempts to maintain authority while Daya is overcome with distress. MacArthur appears, claiming to have an answer regarding the disappearance. He dismissively treats the emotional distress of the others, including Yasuko and Daya, with cold indifference, commanding Shinobu and Shizuka to follow him.\n\nHagoromo and Kaname follow MacArthur through the courtyard and into the outer garden. They walk a significant distance toward a large, calm lake. MacArthur stops and points to the center of the lake, where a small white wooden boat with the number \"2\" written in blue on its bow is floating.",
